page.title: 10YOULSTON PARK
page.content: {Youlston Park}has an area of 100 acres and is directly in front of Youlston Close,which is made up of 1 house and 7 bungalows. Youlston Park used to have many trees in it but recently some have been chopped down. Youlston Park is not a place where children go to play on swings but it is a private estate once owned by the renowned Chichester family. A clump of trees at the front beside the A39 makes the park easily identifiable. The owner of Youlston park lets the park out to other people to keep animals in it and sometimes he will keep deer and other grass eating animals in the park to keep the grass short. The park used to be let out to a cricket team but the owner claimed they were ruining the grass. A major fair has recently been held there.
